==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[γραμμα]]'' meaning "a letter" and ''[[φωνη]]'' meaning "a sound", coined by [[w:Emile Berliner|Emile Berliner]] after the invention of the first [[phonograph]]

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''gramophone'''

# (''Commonwealth'') A [[historic]] [[wind-up]] [[record player]] that records sound on a [[disk]] rather than a [[cylinder]].

===Derived terms===
*[[gramophone record]]
